    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p> <p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into large, bite-size pieces</p> <p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of<strong> boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10 min or until fork-tender</p> <p>Re-boil a kettle</p> <p>&nbsp;</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> eggs</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat (salt prevents the eggs from cracking)</p> <p>Once boiling, boil for exactly&nbsp;8 min for perfect, mid-boiled eggs</p> <p>Once done, cool the<strong> eggs</strong> by running them under <strong>cold water</strong> for 3 min</p> <p>Tip: cooling the eggs completely makes them easier to peel</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the&nbsp;<strong>green beans</strong>&nbsp;in half</p> <p>Rip the&nbsp;<strong>red gem lettuce</strong>&nbsp;into rough bite-size pieces</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the&nbsp;<strong>black olives</strong>&nbsp;roughly</p> <p>Cut the&nbsp;<strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong>&nbsp;in half</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> potatoes</strong> are nearly fork tender, add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong> to the pot and cook for a further 3-4 min or until tender with a slight bite</p> <p>Once done, drain and return to the pot</p> <p>Add a generous drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> with&nbsp;a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> to the<strong> potatoes</strong> and <strong>beans</strong>&nbsp;and mix to combine</p> <p>&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and <strong>dijon mustard</strong> with 3 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> in a small bowl</p> <p>Peel the <strong>garlic</strong> and grate it into the bowl (not a fan of raw garlic? Go easy!) - this is your <strong>french dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and quarter the <strong>cooled eggs</strong></p> <p>Peel the skin from the<strong> smoked mackerel</strong> and discard</p> <p>Break the<strong> smoked mackerel</strong> into rough, bite-size pieces</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/smoky-mackerel-nicoise-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Assemble your ni&ccedil;oise salad with the <strong>red gem</strong>, <strong>eggs</strong>, <strong>olives</strong>, <strong>tomatoes</strong>, <strong>potatoes</strong> and <strong>green beans</strong></p> <p>Drizzle over&nbsp;the<strong> french dressing</strong></p> <p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
